[2] Eye effects
Date: Sun 2 Oct 2016 10:45 am IST
Source: Deccan Chronicle, Asian News International (ANI) report [edited]
http://www.deccanchronicle.com/lifestyle/health-and-wellbeing/021016/experts-say-chikungunya-can-also-affects-the-eye.html


According to Dr Sridevi Gunda, Ophthalmologist at iTek Vision Centre, Noida, eyes have also been seen to be affected [by chikungunya virus infections] in the form of conjunctivitis, uveitis, or episcleritis, retinitis, and optic neuritis wherein the white portion of the eye becomes red. This may or may not be associated with pain.

She further said that in certain cases vision loss can be seen. In initial acute phase pain may be felt at the back of the eye. All the symptoms are self-limiting and paracetamol and certain NSAIDs [nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs] can provide symptomatic relief from fever and pain.

--
